Basic Energy Shares Rise Most in a Month on Study for Geothermal Project

-- B y   I a n   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-03-25T01:58:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/basic-energy-shares-rise-most-in-a-month-on-study-for-geothermal-project.html
Basic Energy Corp. (BSC)  shares climbed
the most in a month in  Manila  trading after the company said it
hired Filtech Energy Drilling Corp. to conduct a so-called pre-
feasibility study for a 20-megawatt geothermal energy project.  The stock increased 3.1 percent to 16.5 centavos as of 9:52
a.m. in Manila, bound for the steepest gain since Feb. 25. The
Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.4 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reinie Booysen at 
